news.title: Bhopal civic body to auction 900 private properties of top defaulters
news.para: The move comes as the civic body aims to increase revenue and recover dues through the city. In spite of the pandemic, BMC has increased its revenue collection in the last three years.

news.title: Property tax to go up for added areas in Trichy
news.para: The areas were formerly with Thiruverumbur town panchayat, Pappakurichi panchayat, Ellakudi panchayat, Keelakalkandar Kottai panchayat and Alathur panchayat.

news.title: Maharashtra govt cancels Nagpur civic body's move to double development charges
news.para: In July 2021, NMC general body too had moved a resolution against the civic administration, directing it to cancel its notification. In 2021, NMC had doubled the development charges in the city with retrospective effect from July 2016.

news.title: Maharashtra government making efforts to speed up slum rehab works: Deputy CM
news.para: Deputy Chief Minister Devendra Fadnavis also said scrutiny was being done, including verification of Aadhaar cards, to weed out names of those dead as well as those ineligible in slum rehabilitation projects.

news.title: Gurugram: Rain pits defunct, town planner seeks action against Countrywide Promoters
news.para: The letter, sent by the district town planner (planning), comes after conducting an enquiry on the complaint of residents about the absence or non-functioning of rainwater harvesting systems in Sector 70A’s BPTP Astaire Garden.

news.title: NCDRC directs ND Developers to refund homebuyers for delay in delivery
news.para: According to the complaint filed with the NCDRC against ND Developers Pvt Ltd and five others, more than 50 homebuyers booked flats at ND Laurel, a housing project at Gunjur, near Varthur in Bengaluru East on March 31, 2011.

news.title: Housing societies in ultra-premium south Mumbai, Bandra localities go in for redevelopment
news.para: These are upscale neighbourhoods where new apartments sell for over Rs 1 lakh a square foot. And chasing these societies are many of the city's A-list developers, rushing to submit their bids to bag lucrative redevelopment projects.

news.title: Noida authority to bring a new policy, may fine builders over layout violations
news.para: ​​The policy, according to sources, will classify the problems that homebuyers face into three broad segments — complaints related to violations of building regulations, those on quality of construction and the third on formation of AOAs and society elections.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh-RERA says it disposed of 9,300 consumer complaints in 2022
news.para: In a statement, the UP RERA said it lodged approximately 6,900 complaints in 2022 and disposed of almost 9,300 complaints of aggrieved allottees.

news.title: Link REIT buys Singapore shopping malls for $1.6 billion
news.para: "This transaction allows us to build a dedicated team in Singapore and provides a base for Link to expand further into other asset classes and strategies in Asia Pacific," Link CEO George Hongchoy said in a statement.

news.title: China Fortune Land sells property units to CR Land in debt restructuring
news.para: The deal comes as Chinese regulators encourage financially sound developers to acquire projects from debt-laden rivals to ease liquidity stress in a sector crucial to China's economy.

news.title: Now, property documents be door-delivered in Chitradurga
news.para: Two villages - Guttinadu and MR Colony under Mattada Kurubarahatti GP limits - were selected for the launch of the initiate, and e-swattu documents were delivered to 80 houses on Wednesday, the CEO said.

news.title: Flat scheme of former NIT trustee on open space: Nagpur society
news.para: Even as the inquiry is under process, a 7-storeyed residential building has come up at the spot. It has been constructed by M/s Ankit Constructions in which Kishor Kanhere, former NCP and current Shiv Sena neta, is a partner as per NIT’s note to UDD.

news.title: Kanpur development body demolishes 12-acre illegal plotting behind Chakeri Airport
news.para: ​The said plotting was being done without seeking sanction of the site plan by the KDA and it was also against the norms of UP Urban Planning and Development Act,1973.

news.title: Puravankara approves issue of NCDs worth up to Rs 230 crore
news.para: The board of directors of Puravankara also approved to invest in Ghar Realty LLP by contributing to 68.26% of the capital of the LLP as designated partner.
